  <h2>Policy Modes</h2>

  <p>
    <code>ValidatingAdmissionPolicyBinding</code> controls validation actions per binding:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Deny</strong> — reject non-compliant resources at admission time. Use for critical security policies.</li>
    <li><strong>Audit</strong> — allow resources but emit audit events. Use during rollout or for informational policies.</li>
    <li><strong>Warn</strong> — allow resources but return a warning to the caller. Useful during migration.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Gradual rollout:</strong> Use <code>Warn</code> mode first to surface violations
      without blocking workloads. Once all existing resources comply, switch to <code>Deny</code>.
      Kubernetes 1.30+ supports all three modes simultaneously on a single binding.
    </p>
  </div>

